# Guard resource-doctype allowlist (REST /api/resource reads; verbs r1 c1 w0 d0 set by govern.sh).
# From the proven live build (12 doctypes): the four governed doctypes + the doctor's read set.
# Sales Order added 2026-07-20 (breadth campaign Wave 1) — a fifth governed doctype, same
# run_method submit/cancel surface as Sales Invoice/Purchase Invoice/Payment Entry.
# Purchase Order added 2026-07-20 (breadth campaign Wave 1) — a sixth governed doctype, same
# run_method submit/cancel surface, mechanically identical to Sales Order.
# Material Request added 2026-07-20 (breadth campaign Wave 1) — a seventh governed doctype, same
# run_method submit/cancel surface; the lowest-risk stock row (no GL/SL of its own, party_field
# =None — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment block).
# Delivery Note added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 1) — an eighth governed doctype, same
# run_method submit/cancel surface; the first STOCK-PRIMARY row (posts both Stock Ledger Entry
# and, conditionally, GL Entry of its own — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment
# block).
# Purchase Receipt added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 1) — a ninth governed doctype, same
# run_method submit/cancel surface; the second STOCK-PRIMARY row (posts both Stock Ledger Entry
# and, conditionally, GL Entry of its own — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment
# block).
# Stock Entry added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 1) — the tenth governed doctype and the LAST
# of Wave 1, same run_method submit/cancel surface; the third STOCK-PRIMARY row and the first
# genuinely polymorphic one (13-way purpose) — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment
# block.
# Supplier Quotation added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 2, first row) — the eleventh governed
# doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; a byte-for-byte mechanical twin of Purchase
# Order (same party_field/submit_via/date_field) — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES
# comment block.
# Quotation added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 2, second row) — the twelfth governed doctype,
# same run_method submit/cancel surface; the FIRST dynamic-party doctype (quotation_to + party_name,
# a Dynamic Link pair — party_field=None, no single static party field to scope by name) — see
# pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment block.
# POS Invoice added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 2, third row) — the thirteenth governed
# doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; byte-for-byte mechanical twin of Sales Invoice's
# SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES entry, but its own submit posts NEITHER a GL Entry NOR a Stock Ledger Entry —
# POSInvoice.on_submit fully overrides SalesInvoice.on_submit without calling it; real GL/SL
# posting is deferred to a separate, later-submitted Sales Invoice a POS Closing Entry builds at
# consolidation — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment block.
# Dunning added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 2, fourth row) — the fourteenth governed
# doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; the FIRST doctype whose native ledger_preview
# RPC this broker skips outright — Dunning has no make_gl_entries method anywhere in its class
# hierarchy (inherits AccountsController, never StockController), so the preview would raise
# AttributeError on a live bench if called; plan_submit reports projected_gl=[] by construction
# instead, with a doctype-gated disclosure naming why — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES
# comment block.
# Stock Reconciliation added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 2, fifth row) — the fifteenth
# governed doctype, and the SECOND to ride SUBMIT_VIA_CLIENT_RPC (frappe.client.submit/.cancel),
# not the run_method surface every doctype since Journal Entry has used: StockReconciliation
# overrides submit()/cancel() themselves, neither decorated @frappe.whitelist(), so the run_method
# vector 403s exactly like Journal Entry's own. Also the first doctype whose native ledger_preview
# RPC is callable and empty but MISLEADING (not honest) — it is absent from ERPNext's own
# SLE-seeding whitelist (unlike Delivery Note/Purchase Receipt/Stock Entry), so the preview never
# seeds the Stock Ledger Entry rows a real submit unconditionally writes; plan_submit carries a
# doctype-gated disclosure naming the false negative — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES
# comment block.
# Landed Cost Voucher added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 2, sixth row and LAST) — the
# sixteenth governed doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; the FIRST doctype whose own
# submit/cancel rewrites OTHER submitted documents' posted ledger rows (the Purchase Receipt/
# Purchase Invoice/Stock Entry/Subcontracting Receipt documents named in its own purchase_receipts
# table are revalued and their Stock Ledger Entry + GL Entry rows reposted, both directions). Its
# native ledger_preview RPC is uncallable (no make_gl_entries anywhere in its class hierarchy —
# LandedCostVoucher(Document), never AccountsController or StockController — the Dunning shape,
# skipped outright) and even a working preview would describe the wrong document, since this
# doctype never posts under its own voucher_type at all; plan_submit AND plan_cancel both carry a
# doctype-gated disclosure naming the real revaluation elsewhere. Its one real cascade edge
# (Landed Cost Purchase Receipt.receipt_document, a Dynamic Link) is genuinely discoverable by the
# generic blast-radius walk (frappe's own live distinct-value resolution, not a static schema
# scan) — a correction against both the pinned dossier and this doctype's own earlier mention in
# Purchase Receipt's landing — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment block.
# Request for Quotation added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 3, first row) — the seventeenth
# governed doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; dispatches to MULTIPLE suppliers via a
# required child table (party_field=None — no single header party); status present, grand_total
# absent, its own eighth _list_fields branch (Material Request's own shape, not a reuse — its
# substitute fields don't exist on this doctype's schema). RFQ is the SO/PO/MR/SQ/Q "honest-empty"
# ledger_preview category, NOT Dunning/LCV's "uncallable" one — it genuinely inherits a real,
# callable make_gl_entries via BuyingController -> SubcontractingController -> StockController, so
# it is NOT added to the ledger_preview skip tuple. on_submit dispatches real email to every
# supplier in the child table — an external-communication side effect, documented as a plan-tier
# disclosure note, never reversed on cancel — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment
# block.
# Blanket Order added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 3, second row) — the eighteenth governed
# doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; carries BOTH customer and supplier as real header
# Link fields, client-side gated by blanket_order_type but NEITHER server-enforced nor server-set
# (party_field=None); status and grand_total both confirmed absent, its own ninth _list_fields
# branch (blanket_order_type + customer/supplier + to_date stand in — the only party=None+absent
# branch that also carries real party context). date_field="from_date" — the first doctype on
# neither the posting_date nor transaction_date pattern. Its native ledger_preview RPC is
# uncallable (BlanketOrder(Document), no make_gl_entries anywhere in its class hierarchy — joins
# the Dunning/Landed Cost Voucher skip tuple) but, unlike LCV, has no revaluation-elsewhere side
# effect on cancel — the simpler Dunning shape. A dossier correction: quotation_item.blanket_order
# is a real Link field the dossier wrongly called non-Link, widening the cascade disclosure surface
# (zero new code either way, cascade.py stays doctype-blind) — see pacioli/erpnext.py's
# SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment block.
# Job Card added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 3, third row) — the nineteenth governed doctype,
# same run_method submit/cancel surface; a shop-floor operation record, zero party fields at all
# (party_field=None); status present (8 options), grand_total absent, its own eleventh
# _list_fields branch (work_order/operation/for_quantity stand in — none of these exist on
# Material Request's or RFQ's own same-shape schemas, so neither is reused). date_field=
# "posting_date" (the default — no new plumbing). Its native ledger_preview RPC is uncallable
# (JobCard(Document), no make_gl_entries anywhere in its class hierarchy — joins the Dunning/
# Landed Cost Voucher/Blanket Order skip tuple) but, like Blanket Order, has no
# revaluation-elsewhere side effect on cancel (on_cancel resets the linked Work Order's operation
# quantities only). A dossier clarification: Material Request's own job_card Link field is the
# same standing shape as Stock Entry's/Purchase Order Item's/both Subcontracting Item doctypes',
# not merely a creation-lineage artifact (zero new code either way, cascade.py stays doctype-blind)
# — see pacioli/erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment block. CAVEAT: Job Card exposes 14 separate
# whitelisted time-log/job-control methods (pause_job, resume_job, start_timer, complete_job_card,
# make_stock_entry, make_stock_entry_for_semi_fg_item, make_subcontracting_po,
# make_material_request, make_corrective_job_card, and others) OUTSIDE this broker's
# submit/cancel/amend surface — this scope grant covers submit/cancel/reads only; it does NOT
# extend to those methods, and no tool is built for any of them.
# BOM added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 3, fourth row) — the twentieth governed doctype,
# same run_method submit/cancel surface; a product recipe/structure, THE FIRST DATELESS DOCTYPE
# (date_field=None — zero Date/Datetime fields across bom.json's 94; the closed-books chain
# branches on the declared pin end to end, equal to ERPNext, which never period-checks BOM).
# party_field=None; status and grand_total both absent (is_active/is_default/total_cost stand in,
# its own twelfth _list_fields branch, no date column at all). Native ledger_preview uncallable
# (BOM(WebsiteGenerator), no make_gl_entries in the MRO — joins the skip tuple). CAVEAT: BOM
# exposes 10 whitelisted methods OUTSIDE the 5-verb surface — sharpest is update_cost, which
# REWRITES A SUBMITTED BOM's stored costs in place and recursively its submitted parents'; also
# make_variant_bom (creates a new BOM). This grant covers submit/cancel/reads only; it does NOT
# extend to those methods, and no tool is built for any of them.
# Work Order added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 3, fifth row) — the twenty-first governed
# doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; an internal manufacturing order
# (party_field=None); status present (10 options), grand_total absent, its own thirteenth
# _list_fields branch (production_item/qty/produced_qty/bom_no stand in). date_field=
# "planned_start_date" — THE FIRST DATETIME-TYPED date field; the broker projects it to its date
# part for the closed-books chain (malformed values stay refused). Native ledger_preview
# uncallable (WorkOrder(Document) — joins the skip tuple). Its own on_cancel refuses while status
# is "Stopped" and while ANY submitted Stock Entry references it. CAVEAT: Work Order exposes 19
# whitelisted methods OUTSIDE the 5-verb surface including TWO submitted-state status mutators —
# stop_unstop (Stopped <-> live) and close_work_order (terminal Closed) — that move the very
# status its own cancel gate keys on, with only base write permission. This grant covers
# submit/cancel/reads only; it does NOT extend to those methods, and no tool is built for any.
# Asset added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 3, sixth row and LAST) — the twenty-second
# governed doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; the first with SCHEDULED ASYNC GL
# (submit arms two channels this broker cannot govern: depreciation JEs via the daily
# post_depreciation_entries scheduler, and the deferred CWIP transfer via the daily
# make_post_gl_entry scheduler for a future available_for_use_date — both disclosed at plan
# time). party_field=None (the asset_owner trio is ownership metadata, not a GL party);
# date_field="available_for_use_date" (the GL posting date; Asset IS in period_closing_doctypes —
# the closed-books check is natively equal to ERPNext). Native ledger_preview CALLABLE (real
# make_gl_entries — NOT in the skip tuple). STRUCTURAL: submit auto-creates and submits an Asset
# Movement linking back, so leaf-node plan_cancel refuses for every submitted Asset —
# plan_cascade_cancel is the governed cancel path (the whole unwind graph, named and consented).
# CAVEAT: Asset exposes 15 whitelisted document-factory methods (make_sales_invoice, split_asset,
# transfer_asset, make_journal_entry, create_asset_repair/_maintenance/_capitalization/
# _value_adjustment, and others) OUTSIDE the 5-verb surface. This grant covers submit/cancel/
# reads only; it does NOT extend to those methods, and no tool is built for any of them.
# Packing Slip added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 4, first row) — the twenty-third governed
# doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; a shipment-packing record, zero party fields at
# all (party_field=None; delivery_note is a Link AT a Delivery Note, not a party). status and
# grand_total both absent; its own fifteenth _list_fields branch (delivery_note/from_case_no/
# to_case_no stand in) is also the FIRST to omit "company" from the requested columns — Packing
# Slip carries no company field either (see below). date_field=None — THE SECOND DATELESS
# doctype (reuses BOM's own NO_DATE_FIELD machinery unchanged). Native ledger_preview uncallable
# (PackingSlip(StatusUpdater), no make_gl_entries in the MRO — joins the skip tuple); on_submit/
# on_cancel both rewrite a packed_qty COUNTER on the linked Delivery Note Item/Packed Item via a
# raw SQL update, never a GL row. CASCADE LEAF: the only Link -> Packing Slip field anywhere in
# the tree is its own self-referencing amended_from — no other doctype can ever block this
# doctype's own cancel. NEW FINDING (not new machinery): Packing Slip also carries no "company"
# field, so a company-PINNED target correctly refuses every governed write on it ("wrong books" —
# None never matches a real pin); only an UNPINNED target (registry.py's documented posture) can
# govern it. Reads (get/list) are unaffected either way. CAVEAT: ONE read-only whitelisted method
# (item_details, a search filter) — nothing to withhold, the smallest side surface yet.
# Cost Center Allocation added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 4, second row) — the
# twenty-fourth governed doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; a recurring-allocation
# RULE, zero party fields at all (party_field=None; main_cost_center/company are structural
# routing fields, not a party). status and grand_total both absent; its own sixteenth
# _list_fields branch (main_cost_center/valid_from stand in, no substitute/context column exists
# at all — the smallest schema this campaign has found, 7 fields total). date_field="valid_from"
# — A DOSSIER CORRECTION: the dossier claimed this doctype was both dated AND "dateless"; settled
# from source as an ORDINARY dated doctype (a real, required Date field, default "Today") — the
# sixth distinct date-fieldname pattern, riding the existing generic date machinery unchanged,
# never the NO_DATE_FIELD sentinel. Unlike Packing Slip, "company" DOES exist here (fetched from
# main_cost_center, reqd) — the standing "wrong books" belt applies in its ordinary form, no new
# machinery. Native ledger_preview uncallable (a direct Document subclass, no make_gl_entries in
# the MRO — joins the skip tuple); NO on_submit/on_cancel hook of any kind is defined — the
# simplest submit/cancel lifecycle this campaign has found, never even a counter rewrite. CASCADE
# LEAF: the only Link -> Cost Center Allocation field anywhere in the tree is its own
# self-referencing amended_from. CAVEAT: ZERO whitelisted methods — nothing to withhold, smaller
# even than Packing Slip's one read-only search filter.
# Supplier Scorecard Period added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 4, third row) — the
# twenty-fifth governed doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; Wave 4's FIRST ROW WITH A
# REAL PARTY FIELD (party_field="supplier", a required header-level Link — Packing Slip/Cost
# Center Allocation both carried party_field=None). status and grand_total both absent
# (total_score, a Percent, is a SCORE, never a monetary substitute); its own seventeenth
# _list_fields branch. date_field="start_date" (a real, required Date field, chosen over the
# doctype's own end_date as the period's anchor) — the seventh distinct date-fieldname pattern.
# "company" is CONFIRMED ABSENT — a dossier omission, the SECOND companyless doctype after
