# Allocation established). CASCADE LEAF: the only Link -> Supplier Scorecard Period field
# anywhere in the tree is its own self-referencing amended_from (the parent Supplier Scorecard
# relationship runs the OTHER way — this doctype's own `scorecard` field links TO it). CAVEAT:
# ZERO whitelisted methods — nothing to withhold. A SEPARATE caveat load-bearing to the whole
# doctype: it is ordinarily MACHINE-GENERATED AND MACHINE-SUBMITTED by its own parent Supplier
# Scorecard doctype (on every parent save, and once daily via the refresh_scorecards scheduled
# job) — never by this broker, a dossier §11 omission (its RED FLAGS scan never checked the
# parent doctype).
# Quality Inspection added 2026-07-21 (breadth campaign Wave 4, fourth row) — the twenty-sixth
# governed doctype, same run_method submit/cancel surface; the FIRST DOCTYPE ON A DYNAMIC LINK
# PAIR since Quotation (party_field=None — reference_type/reference_name, never a static party).
# status present (Accepted/Rejected/Cancelled, default Accepted); grand_total absent (a pure
# control/quality record, never a transaction) — its own eighteenth _list_fields branch.
# date_field="report_date" (real, required, default Today) — the EIGHTH distinct date-fieldname
# pattern. company IS present (unlike Packing Slip/Supplier Scorecard Period) though not reqd —
# set programmatically from the reference document; a dossier "GL party fixture" framing
# corrected (this doctype posts no GL at all). Native ledger_preview UNCALLABLE (a direct
# Document subclass, no make_gl_entries anywhere in either the erpnext-16 or frappe-16 checkouts
# — joins the skip tuple). before_submit THROWS if any readings row lacks its own status value
# — a genuine dossier omission (its own §4/§6 never mention this hook), disclosed as a
# doctype-scoped submit risk flag. on_cancel unconditionally rewrites the reference document's
